caption.text:
Burnin‚Äô the midnight candle in the IP üïØÔ∏è 
Bench press at the END of my chest training. 
Depending on how I feel, I‚Äôll often end training major parts (chest, back, legs) with a compound movement that very strict and slow with a 3:1 tempo (3 second negative, 1 sec pause). 
Great activation and because I‚Äôm fatigued at this point, it forces me to really concentrate on mind muscle connection - and not be a little bitch because of the pain üòÇüí™üèæ 

Give bench (or any press) wide grip pull ups/downs and squats a try at the end of your training. You‚Äôll make some good progress + you also wont need to load the bar up with a lot of weight. 

#ironparadise üïØÔ∏è
#wherejesusjustleftchicago

caption.text:
I know, I know this may sound corny‚Ä¶

but you guys hear me say this all the time when it comes to things like this‚Ä¶

meeting people and hearing about their journeys of weight loss, mental health struggles, fitness, dealing with loss, anxiety, depression, hard times etc etc 

moments Iike this become my profound reminder that this is the best part of fame‚Ä¶ 

Keep up the great work Jonny Cleasby, not only have you changed your life, but your journey will change many lives who you‚Äôll go on to touch, as you roll on down the road of life. 

Happy birthday dude, go crush cake & tequila üòâüç∞ü•É

~ dj 

#bestpartoffame
